Source: pg-stat-backtrace
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), libunwind-dev, pkg-config
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/Nickyoung0/pg_stat_backtrace

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-stat-backtrace
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pg-stat-backtrace
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Capture C-level backtraces of PostgreSQL processes
  pg_stat_backtrace exposes SQL functions to capture or log the C-level stack
  backtrace of PostgreSQL processes on Linux using ptrace and libunwind.
  Runtime use depends on host ptrace policy such as kernel.yama.ptrace_scope.
